{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing slot assignment in pnf_handle_ul_dci_request function\n\n### Summary\nIn the NR PNF P7 handling code, the `pnf_handle_ul_dci_request` function was not properly storing the slot information in the slot buffer. While it correctly set the SFN field, it was missing the assignment of the Slot field to `pnf_p7->slot_buffer[buffer_index].slot`. This caused UL DCI requests to be processed with incorrect slot information, leading to missed or delayed uplink transmissions.\n\nThe issue was identified by comparing with similar functions like `pnf_handle_dl_tti_request`, `pnf_handle_ul_tti_request`, and `pnf_handle_tx_data_request` which all correctly set both SFN and Slot fields.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/pnf/src/pnf_p7.c`: Added missing slot assignment in `pnf_handle_ul_dci_request` function:\n  ```c\n  pnf_p7->slot_buffer[buffer_index].slot = req->Slot;\n  ```\n\nThis ensures UL DCI requests are properly stored with complete timing information and can be correctly processed later in the transmission pipeline.\n"
}